Task 3:Types of Linux Shells

Linux distributions come with several types of shells, each with its own unique set of features. You can use the echo $SHELL command to see which shell you are currently using. Additionally, the file /etc/shells lists all available shells on your system. Some popular shells include:
Current Shell

user@ubuntu:~$ echo $SHELL
/bin/bash
